# GUM — Google Universal MCP

This project uses **gum** to expose Google APIs and curated plugins as a small,
token-efficient MCP tool surface. Treat this file as the project's context note
for any AI agent that connects to the gum MCP server (`gum mcp --stdio`).

Generated by `gum init` (version: {{.GumVersion}}).
Refresh on upgrade: `gum init --refresh`.

## How gum is shaped

gum collapses the entire Google + plugin surface into a Tier A roster of
**9 meta-tools + 18 convenience tools**. Token budget: ≤8000 tokens for the
full tier (spec §2). Output is TOON-shaped by default for uniform-array
responses; opaque payloads fall back to JSON.

### Meta-tools

| Tool                 | Risk class    | When to use                                                |
|----------------------|---------------|-----------------------------------------------------------|
| `gum.search_apis`    | read          | Find an op_id by keyword across the full catalog.          |
| `gum.describe_op`    | read          | Print one op's variants, schemas, scopes, risk class.      |
| `gum.read`           | read          | Invoke a `risk_class="read"` variant.                      |
| `gum.write`          | write         | Invoke a `risk_class="write"` variant (confirmation gate). |
| `gum.destructive`    | destructive   | Invoke a `risk_class="destructive"` variant (HMAC token).  |
| `gum.code`           | code          | Run a Risor program against the same dispatch kernel.      |
| `gum.poll`           | read          | Poll a long-running operation handle.                      |
| `gum.cache_stats`    | read          | Inspect the semantic / HTTP / prompt cache counters.       |
| `gum.gain`           | read          | Read the token-savings ledger for the active profile.      |

### Convenience tools (Tier A)

`gmail_search`, `gmail_get_message`, `gmail_send`, `gmail_create_draft`,
`drive_find`, `drive_get_file`, `drive_share`,
`calendar_upcoming`, `calendar_create_event`, `calendar_update_event`,
`docs_get`, `docs_create`, `sheets_read`, `sheets_write`, `slides_get`,
`tasks_list`, `tasks_create`, `flights_search`.

Every convenience tool is a sugar wrapper over a single catalog variant; use
`gum.describe_op` to inspect its `op_id`, scopes, and risk class.

## Risk-gate contract

The risk class is on the **variant**, not the caller. If you call
`gum.read("docs.documents.update", ...)`, the dispatcher rejects with
`RISK_TOOL_MISMATCH` before any HTTP request. Retry through `gum.write`
or `gum.destructive` to match the resolved variant's class.

Confirmation envelopes (`requires_confirmation: true`) carry an HMAC-signed
token; re-invoke with `confirmed: true` and `confirmation_token: <token>`
within 5 minutes.

## Profile selection

A profile binds **one** credential + one config to **one** gum process for
its entire lifetime. Switch profiles by starting a new process:

```bash
gum --profile work mcp --stdio       # MCP server bound to 'work' profile
gum --profile personal call docs.get ...
```

Per-profile state lives under:

- `~/.config/gum/<profile>/config.toml`  — settings (mode 600)
- `~/.local/share/gum/<profile>/`        — audit log, gain ledger, tee artifacts
- OS keychain `gum/<profile>`            — refresh tokens, plugin secrets

## Auth method

Pick one strategy per profile:

| Strategy           | Setup command                                  | When                                              |
|--------------------|------------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------|
| `gum_oauth`        | `gum auth login`                               | Default. Browser PKCE; built-in client; keychain. |
| `byo_oauth`        | `gum auth setup <op_id>`                       | Custom OAuth client (e.g., publisher requires it).|
| `adc`              | `gum auth use-adc`                             | Server / CI. Reads ADC; never auto-consumed.      |
| `service_account`  | `gum auth use-service-account key.json`        | Workspace domain-wide or service identity.        |
| `api_key`          | `gum auth use-api-key <key>`                   | Unauthenticated / public APIs.                    |
| `compound`         | Per-plugin: see `gum plugin setup <name>`      | Plugins with developer-token + OAuth + ...        |

`gum init` never silently consumes ambient `GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS`;
opt in with `gum auth use-adc` on the profile that should accept ADC.

## Token-budget guarantees

- Tier A roster is fixed at ≤8000 cl100k_base tokens.
- Catalog/plugin shaping uses TOON for uniform arrays + `_expression` envelopes.
- Inspect savings: `gum gain`. Replay release fixtures: `gum gain --fixture-replay`.

## Configuration examples

### Read-only profile

`~/.config/gum/read-only/config.toml`

```toml
config_schema_version = 1

[profile]
description = "Read-only access — gum.read + convenience read tools only"

[auth]
strategy = "gum_oauth"
# Run: gum --profile read-only auth login

[gain]
enabled = true
```

### Write-enabled profile

`~/.config/gum/work/config.toml`

```toml
config_schema_version = 1

[profile]
description = "Daily-use profile with write access"

[auth]
strategy = "gum_oauth"

[gain]
enabled = true

# Plugin allow-list (only listed plugins load; comment out to allow all).
# [[plugin]]
# name = "flights"
```

### Code-mode profile

`~/.config/gum/automation/config.toml`

```toml
config_schema_version = 1

[profile]
description = "Automation profile — allows gum.code with write side effects"

[auth]
strategy = "service_account"
# Run: gum --profile automation auth use-service-account /path/to/key.json

[code]
# Maximum cumulative stdout/stderr bytes from gum.code (spec §6.1.2).
output_limit_bytes = 1048576

[gain]
enabled = true
```

## Useful commands

```bash
gum mcp --stdio                       # Start the MCP server (Claude Code, Cursor, ...)
gum call <op_id> --risk=read ...      # CLI direct dispatch
gum describe <op_id>                  # Variant + schema details
gum profile validate                  # Lint expression profiles
gum cache stats --format=json         # Inspect cache layers
gum gain                              # Token-savings summary
```

See `gum --help` for the full surface.
